<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1435,1609,1706]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
One of the most widespread species in the Kimberley (and 
<collectingCountry box="[819,926,1609,1633]" name="Australia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Australia</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[945,1227,1609,1633]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Terapontidae" genus="Leiopotherapon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis box="[945,1227,1609,1633]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Leiopotherapon unicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been captured from all the major river systems and their tributaries in the region (
<figureCitation box="[908,993,1645,1669]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="49.[151,250,1502,1525]" captionTargetBox="[259,1327,195,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-23@49.[257,1330,193,1481]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURE 32. Distribution of Leiopotherapon unicolor in the Kimberley." pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). The species is usually more abundant in tributaries than main-channel sites within the Kimberley (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Morgan, D. &amp; Cheinmora, D. &amp; Charles, A. &amp; Nulgit, P. &amp; Kimberley Language Resource Centre" box="[870,1087,1681,1706]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref19400" refString="Morgan, D., Cheinmora, D., Charles, A., Nulgit, P. &amp; Kimberley Language Resource Centre. (2006) Fishes of the King Edward and Carson Rivers with their Belaa and Ngarinyin names. Murdoch University, Kimberley Language Resource Centre, Land &amp; Water Australia Project No. UMU 22. http: // www. cffr. murdoch. edu. au / reports / King _ Edward _ fishes _ final _ report. pdf" type="journal volume" year="2006">
Morgan 
<emphasis box="[965,1014,1681,1705]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
, Morgan in press).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
